bio:

My love for beauty has carried me through the hardest of times, introduced to my passion, people, amazing brands, & taught me lessons. Most importantly, given me the confidence and self love that i struggled to find for so long. 

I currently have a collective outreach around 30,000 gorgeous & supportive individuals, Instagram being my main platform. 
Also 25,000 views on my Youtube channel. 
I took a bit of a break from social media after the loss of my mother. 

I'm looking to build some new relationships with brands for the blog i have in the works. Doing so would enable me to deliver some fresh content within my current channels, and of course grow as a whole. The majority of my subscribers are young women that are active in social media for the latest health & beauty trends, tips, products and reviews. 

Marc Jacobs Beauty, Anastasia Beverly hills, Sigma, Melt Cosmetics, Limecrime, Instyler, are a few of many brands I've been recognized by and/or worked with. 

I've received promotional PR packages and opportunity offers such as pro memberships with cosmetic companies , compensation for advertising and even a spot working in New York for fashion week. 

I truly am a "people person", I care about others and I am genuine with a good heart. To me this is a rarity in this day in age, and the only way to stay true to who I am. Ive grown a personal bond with my supporters, like a 2nd family. Im ready for what the future holds,

name: Kid Chris
bio:
Globetrotter Kid Chris excites audiences in Europe, Asia, Africa and the USA in more than 60 countries, hundreds of cities with more than 150 gigs each year.. The selection of clubs, venues and festivals he performed, as a headline Dj is endless. He is the dj of the successful event series “In Bed with Space World Tour”. Born, raised and based in Cologne/ Germany, he loves to travels the world, always bringing good music and happiness with him. 
With his inimitable and pushing sound, he animates and excites every party crowd all over the globe. An irresistible mix of high quality and uplifting electronic dance music. The unique Kid Chris Sound is Ibiza influenced and combined with high energy club anthems and his breathtaking vocalist and mc live performance. 
The start of the year 2012 was more than perfect for Kid Chris. His upcoming single “Stardust” is signed to one of the world’s leading Dance Labels “WE PLAY” and killer melody peak time anthem (release coming soon). Since March 2012 in stores: The Kid Chris remix of the all time House Music Classic: “Mighty Dub Katz – Magic Carpet Ride”. The alter ego behind the Mighty Dub Katz is no one else than the Musician “Norman Cook” aka “FATBOY SLIM”. The remix is part of Fatboy Slim’s new Mix Album “Dance Harder Bitch”. Back in 2007 Kid Chris’ debut Single “South Beach” was a huge club anthem, supported by dj's such as Paul van Dyk, Roger Sanchez, Micha Moor and many more others. Kid Chris remixed Fat Boy Slim/ Mighty Dub Katz, Barbara Tucker, Lissat & Voltaxx, Alexandra Prince, Plastik Funk and the German pop act “Rosenstolz” to name a few. With success: His interpretation of the Prodigy Remake „No Good“ from Sean Finn (WE PLAY), took place for 5 weeks on chart position #1 of the german dance charts in summer 2011. Furthermore his Remix “Gib mir Sonne” from Rosenstolz (August 2008) reached the billboard chart position #1 in Germany, Switzerland and Austria and has Gold Status. 
World leading Dance Music Labels by way of example: Ministry of Sound, Toolroom, We Play, Universal, Milk & Sugar, Pacha Recordings (Ibiza), Blanco Y Negro, Ultra Rec., Southern Fried Rec., and more signed Kid Chris for releases, remixes and compilations with great success and chart placements in Europe, Asia, U.A.E., Russia and U.S.A.. 
His music productions are featured on compilations: 
Dance Harder Bitch – mixed by Fatboy Slim (Mighty Dub Katz – Magic Carpet Ride – Kid Chris & Brian Cribbs Remix), Big FM Tronic Love mixed by Hanna Hansen: (Sean Finn - No Good – Kid Chris Remix), Ministry of Sound The Annual (Geo da Silva – I’ll do it like a Truck – Kid Chris Remix), Cream Ibiza, Mixed by Paul van Dyk (Kid Chris – South Beach- Original), Pure Pacha Ibiza and Pacha Ibiza VIP Vol. 2 (Mixed by Sarah Main: Guernica – Darkness - Kid Chris Remix) to mention some references. 
October 2008 Kid Chris released his first mix compilation album “In Touch with Ibiza Vol. 1“ (Clubstar Rec.). The CD was a huge success and sold out in a few month. “In Touch with Ibiza Vol. 2“ in 2009 and Vol. 3 in 2010 followed. All Cd’s were bestseller’s in Music stores around the world and took place in the Beatport, Amazon and Itunes Sale Charts. In 2011 Kid Chris released the Mix Album „“In Bed with Space Vol. 14“ together with the world famous Dj Duo “Dabruck & Klein“. The Cd was also a bestseller. Two new mix albums are planned for the year 2012. 
Kid Chris performed alongside the biggest names of the scene: David Guetta, Fedde le Grand, Snoop Dog, Eddie Thoneick, Michael Gray, Pete Tong, John Dahlback, Barbara Tucker, Jerome Ismaee, Carl Cox, Erick Morillo, David Morales, Todd Terry, Westbam, Lexy & K. Paul, Michael Gray, Eddie Thoneick, D.o.n.s., Milk and Sugar, Disco Boys, Kurd Maverick, Dabruck & Klein, Dj Antoine and many more. 
Regular Gigs in the most famous and extravagant clubs around the globe: Space Club and Privilege Ibiza (Spain), Pacha Marrakesh (Morocco), Velvet and Cocoon Club in Frankfurt (Germany), Set Club and Club 50 Viceroy in Miami (U.S.A.), Attica (Singapore), Bed Supper Club in Bangkok (Thailand), Sankeys Manchester and That Club London in (U.K.), SPACEdance in Mykonos (Greece), Answer Club in Seoul (South Korea), Aquarius club Zrce and Zagreb (Croatia), Panama in Amsterdam (Holland), Loft in Malaysia (Kuala Lumpur), Halikarnas in Bodrum (Turkey), Chillout Club Luanda (Angola) (extracts). 
Furthermore for events as follows: In Bed With Space, in Touch With Ibiza, The Original White Party from Amsterdam, Ministry of Sound Club Tour (Germany), MTV Becks Gold Tour, MTV Kia Soul Tour, MTV Asia (Live in Singapore), MTV Austria (Music and Style/ Donauinselfest), Viva TV (Style Nights) and Viva Club Rotation (Poland, U.K., Germany and Spain, Ibiza), Rich Glamour Night (Rich Prosecco) and of course in the course the world’s most important conference for electronic dance music: Winter Music Conference in Miami USA and Amsterdam Dance Event in Holland, Europe.

name: ALEXX MACK
bio:
Fun, edgy and boisterous are leading characteristics that help make up the unique creative DNA of rising pop artist, ALEXX MACK. Having dedicated time to personally develop her craft of songwriting and artistry, Alexx is set to impact the music scene with an infectious blend of appealing electronic, alternative and pop elements. Most recently, Alexx independently released her highly anticipated EP, "Like We're Famous" – a flirtatious and infectious collection of songs that have received accolades from leading industry outlets such as Billboard, Spin, Paper Mag, Idolator and Noisey Vice. 

Born in Atlanta, Georgia, and raised in Jupiter, Florida, Alexx was introduced to her passion for music at a very early age. By the age of only seven, Alexx began penning her own songs and continued to develop her writing the same time as she was exploring her individuality. Witnessing the talent at hand, her parents encouraged Alexx to pursue music seriously throughout her education. Graduating from high school a year early, Alexx headed west to LA where she was quickly inspired by the energy and creativity of her new surroundings. Through collaborating with local producers and writers, Alexx recorded early competitive material that found its way to influential taste makers and industry professionals. In a short amount of time, Alexx secured a world-wide publishing deal with BMG, which then in turn allowed her the independence to identify her own brand as an artist. 

Since the release of “Like We’re Famous,” Alexx has been featured on leading outlets such as BBC Radio 1, iHeart Media and SiriusXM. In March, 2016, Alexx released a remix of “Sunglasses” with DJ/Producer GOLDHOUSE. Also in March, Alexx performed two shows at South by Southwest, to rave reviews. In addition to her solo efforts, Alexx collaborated with DJ/Producer John Dahlback on his Armada Records EDM single, “Count To Ten,” which has amassed over 1,000,000 plays on Spotify. Alexx is currently in the studio writing for her next release in late 2016.

name: The Mixed Medic
bio:
TMM is a personal blog that looks at the science behind the hype and combines Western approaches to medicine with Eastern philosophies about wellness and mindfulness, taking care of ourselves inside and out. It provides nutritious bites of information that may help readers make more informed decisions about their lifestyles, or may simply serve as an entertaining read. 

Unlike the stereotypical health/fitness fanatic, I am not a body building, gym junkie that eats out of plastic containers, nor a gluten-free, paleo, vegan orthorexic recovering from autoimmune disease or a self-confessed life guru and yogi addict proclaiming to be the next Dalai Lama. My family’s motto is ‘everything in moderation’ and I started writing this blog to further educate myself about the food I eat, the cosmetics I love and the things I do. As someone who grew up being fed the stressful London lifestyle, I like researching ways to help myself be more mindful and take care of myself mentally and physically, in an increasingly manic world. I hope that you may find some of the articles on here applicable and useful to you too!

name: FairyTalesNails
bio:
My name is Kirsty I'm 24 years old and a full-time mummy to my beautiful baby girl Lexi. I am also a nail polish addict and baking fanatic, since having my little girl I wanted to do something that was just for me. 

Because I have the worst oven in the world my baking hobby is not as easily fulfilled anymore, and having a child running around doesn't allow me a lot of time to worry about a rising cake. 

So after much deliberation I looked down at my fingers and decided I was going to stop being a nail biter and become a nail stamper. The idea was if my nails looked pretty then I wouldn't want to bite them, so far so good. 

My collection started out with a few Barry M's and some stamping plates, this however took on a momentum of its own and before I knew it I had a Helmer full of nail polish, a massive stamping plate library and a box full of nail art goodies. 

It is absolutely fair to say I am in love and an addict! It's almost a year later and I have decided to start writing a nail blog to share with all of you fellow nail addicts in the world. I hope you enjoy my ramblings and we can share our love of all things nail related. 

Let's share in the madness and have lots of fun.

name: Markus Kenzie
bio:
Markus Kenzie, geboren in Johannesburg/ Südafrika und aufgewachsen in Berlin. Arbeitet seit über 7 Jahren erfolgreich als androgynes Model für große und namenhafte Labels, insbesondere im asiatischen Raum kann Markus eine beachtliche Karriere vorweisen. Durch seinen speziellen Unisex Look setzte er vor allem in Japan Maßstäbe und arbeitete dort für u.a. Yamamoto und UniQlo. 
Anfangs war es sehr schwer sich als androgynes Model in Deutschland durchzusetzen, aber mit Ausdauer und Durchsetzungsvermögen, lief er unzählige Shows, auch auf der Mercedes Benz Fashion Week in Berlin, setze somit einen neuen Baustein in Deutschland. Durch die Kampagne für das Lifestyle Label Schwarzer Reiter, wo er bis heut als das Aushängeschild und Hausmodel tätig ist, machte er sich innerhalb der Fashionbranche einen Namen. 
Markus sucht und liebt die Abwechslung, begibt sich neuen Herausforderungen, wie seine Zigaretten switchte er nach und nach in die TV Welt und war lange Zeit Werbegesicht für das Möbelhaus Roller und agierte als Co Moderator bei der RTL Primetime Samstagabendshow " Die Thorsten Havenner Show ". Er drehte des Weiteren das Shopping Queen Special und Aschenputtel Experiment und konnte so den Zuschauern das erste mal seine charakterlichen Züge zeigen und gewann mit seiner rotzigen aber sympathischen Berlinergörren Art die Herzen der Zuschauer. 
Das Potential von Markus erkennen auch immer mehr Marken, welche Markus als Influencer auf Instagram buchen. Oder ihn als gern gesehenen Gast für die wichtigsten Medien Events, wie Bambi Verleihung, Dresdner Semperopernball, Filmpremieren (u.a. Tribute von Panem, The Hateful 8 ) , einladen. 
Neben seiner Arbeit als Model und unterschiedlichen TV Projekten konzentriert sich Markus aktuell als Influencer auf sein Instagram Profil und baut seinen eigenen Youtube Kanal aus.

name: Vegan Sustainable Life
bio:
Advocating for a more mindful way of living, shopping, and eating. 

I’m Tajda and I moved to Manchester, UK exactly 3 weeks ago. Veganism has had such a positive influence on my life. I see it as something that’s closely related to a broader spectrum of movements such as the low waste movement, mindfulness, and slow fashion. I’m always happy to spread the message about the positive sides of being a vegan, but I'm not here to preach. What makes plant-based living such a fulfilling lifestyle for me is the fact that it's all about connecting with your community, finding joy in little things (like no milk powder on the ingredients list, right?!) and getting in touch with your own needs while learning from your mistakes. 

I run a creative platform My Vegan Minimalist (@myveganminimalist) where I advocate for a more mindful way of eating, living, and shopping. This blog is my tiny little baby and it really unleashed the creativity I never knew I could share with the world. If you're just new to it or struggling with veganism, I definitely encourage you to get involved with the online community. 

My work as a writer and photographer is influenced by a number of my interests; such as fair fashion (I founded a sustainable clothing brand Knit And Green @knitandgreen), minimalism and sustainability. Thank you to my loves The Vegan Map for letting me share this with all of you, I love reading each and every piece on here

name: The Main Street Mouse - Michele
bio:
Michele Atwood is a life-long Disney Enthusiast and fan who has turned her love of all things Disney into a full time job. Born in Michigan, Michele began traveling to Disney World with her family as a child, and started taking regular trips ever since. Michele has an educational background in Finance, and worked in the Investment Banking field until 2010. Michele also was self employed by making Disney themed accessories and worked the art show circuit for her business, Cindershella’s Boutique. With Disney at the forefront, she decided to share her love of The Mouse with others and create The Main Street Mouse back in late 2009. The idea for the site came during a trip to the Walt Disney World Resort with her husband Scott in 2008. The goal Michele had was to create a place for Disney Fans to congregate and share Disney Information, as well as their own personal memories and stories. Also, keeping in mind her two sons, Andrew and Aidan, who she also groomed to be Disney Enthusiasts, she wanted to make TMSM a place for Disney Fans of all ages. 

In March of 2017, Michele’s first book, “Moving to Main Street, U.S.A.” was released and has done very well right out of the gate. After receiving feedback on the book and on her “Disney in the City, Confessions of a Grown Up Disney Princess” articles featured in The Main Street Monthly Magazine, the idea to launch micheleatwood.com aka Princess in the City was born. In this new lifestyle blog, readers can enjoy articles on home life, fashion, cosmetics, pop culture, life/mommy issues, current events, random ramblings and so much more!
